Interface Harbor

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, HarborTypes, Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    HarborStub

    public interface Harbor
extends Service, HarborTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The Harbor interface provides methods to manage the lifecycle of an integrated Harbor container registry in vCenter.

    • Method Detail

      • create

        Harbor.CreateInvocation create(HarborTypes.CreateSpec spec)
        Creates a Harbor registry in the cluster.

        Invocation Result:
        Identifier of the deployed registry. The return value will be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.content.Registry.

        Parameters:
        spec - Specification for creating the Harbor registry.
        Returns:
        instance of Harbor.CreateInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described create operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        AlreadyExists - if a Harbor already exists in the associated cluster.
        NotFound - if resources/objects could not be located.
        Unsupported - if HarborTypes.CreateSpec.getCluster() does not have vSphere namespace enabled.
        InvalidArgument - if spec contains any errors.
        Error - if the system reports an error while responding to the request.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if the user does not have ContentLibrary.ManageRegistry and/or CertificateAuthority.Manage privilege, or user does not have ContentLibrary.ManageClusterRegistryResource privilege on HarborTypes.CreateSpec.getCluster().

      • delete

        Harbor.DeleteInvocation delete(java.lang.String registry)
        Delete the Harbor registry in the cluster. All Harbor projects, repositories and images will be deleted upon Harbor registry deletion.
        Parameters:
        registry - Identifier of the registry. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.content.Registry.
        Returns:
        instance of Harbor.DeleteInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described delete operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        NotFound - if a registry specified by registry could not be found.
        Error - if the system reports an error while responding to the request.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if the user does not have ContentLibrary.ManageRegistry privilege.

        Harbor.GetInvocation get(java.lang.String registry)
        Get detailed information of the Harbor registry.

        Invocation Result:
        Information about the registry.

        Parameters:
        registry - Identifier of the registry. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.content.Registry.
        Returns:
        instance of Harbor.GetInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described get operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:

        Error - if the system reports an error while responding to the request.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
